WEBVTT

00:03.567 --> 00:04.567
[ Cellphone chimes ]

00:04.568 --> 00:06.686
Ah.
David just parked.

00:06.687 --> 00:08.686
You know, I don't think
I've ever met Mark's dad.

00:08.687 --> 00:11.026
Well, we've actually been
separated for years,

00:11.027 --> 00:13.856
so he's never been
to a parent-teacher
conference before.

00:13.857 --> 00:15.686
He was
working overseas.
Oh.

00:15.687 --> 00:18.686
Not for money, but, um...

00:18.687 --> 00:19.687
But he's a good dad...
yeah.

00:19.688 --> 00:21.687
Not a <i> great</i> dad,
or he would've been on time.

00:23.687 --> 00:24.197
I'm just -- I'm just kidding.

00:24.198 --> 00:25.686
I'm just kidding.

00:25.687 --> 00:27.196
We have that kind
of relationship,

00:27.197 --> 00:28.687
you know, when he's not around.

00:30.687 --> 00:32.686
Oh, so, so sorry we're late.

00:32.686 --> 00:33.856
Who's this?

00:33.857 --> 00:35.686
This is my girlfriend, Blue.

00:35.687 --> 00:36.687
Blue, this is Darlene,

00:36.688 --> 00:40.415
and -- and Mark's teacher,
Mrs... um, Reynolds.

00:40.417 --> 00:42.246
Thank you for having me,

00:42.247 --> 00:45.127
member of
the noblest profession.

00:46.417 --> 00:50.246
Ah, and it's so nice
to finally meet <i> you,</i> Darlene.

00:50.247 --> 00:53.246
Yes, it's...
nice to meet you, too.

00:53.247 --> 00:55.757
And what a delightful surprise
that it's happening here!

00:58.247 --> 01:00.126
I should've told you
that Blue was coming,

01:00.127 --> 01:01.246
but at the last minute,

01:01.247 --> 01:03.246
she felt that --

01:03.247 --> 01:05.245
I-I mean <i> we</i> felt
that if she was here,

01:05.247 --> 01:07.246
she could be
a more profound part

01:07.247 --> 01:09.246
of Mark's life journey.

01:09.247 --> 01:11.246
Yeah, I've only met Mark twice,

01:11.247 --> 01:13.257
but I've known him forever.

01:15.247 --> 01:18.247
And, you know, like
they say, the more
parents, the better!

01:20.127 --> 01:22.956
Um... who says that?
No one says that.

01:22.957 --> 01:24.246
So, why don't we get started.

01:24.247 --> 01:26.246
Uh, yeah, sorry.

01:26.247 --> 01:28.246
I'm -- I'm anxious
to hear how Mark's
doing in his new class.

01:28.247 --> 01:31.246
First, Mark is
an absolute pleasure,

01:31.247 --> 01:33.246
although he <i> can</i> be...
a little too talkative at times.

01:33.247 --> 01:35.247
That is so Mark.

01:37.247 --> 01:41.256
I'm always saying that.
He's so highly verbal.

01:41.257 --> 01:44.247
Totally. You would
know, 'cause you've
met him twice, so...

01:45.247 --> 01:48.246
So, uh...
Mark's a big talker?

01:48.247 --> 01:50.246
Is that -- Is that
affecting his schoolwork?

01:50.247 --> 01:53.246
No. Honestly, it's a struggle
to keep him challenged.

01:53.247 --> 01:54.247
W-W-Well, you know,
if you think

01:54.248 --> 01:56.246
he needs some extra work
to challenge him,

01:56.247 --> 01:58.246
we can help him when the kids
stay over this weekend.

01:58.247 --> 02:00.246
H-Hold up. What --
The kids are staying over?

02:00.247 --> 02:01.587
I never agreed to that.

02:04.247 --> 02:07.246
Huh. My smart watch is telling
me to get up and move,

02:07.247 --> 02:08.417
and, I don't know,
<i>now</i> seems like a good time.

02:11.247 --> 02:13.416
You said the kids
could sleep over sometimes.

02:13.417 --> 02:15.756
That's just
something you say, like,

02:15.757 --> 02:17.247
"They're your kids, too."

02:19.127 --> 02:20.246
Come on.

02:20.247 --> 02:21.257
I'm trying to make up
for lost time here.

02:24.957 --> 02:27.246
Fine.
They can sleep over.

02:27.247 --> 02:30.246
[ Chuckles ] And you do
not have to worry.

02:30.247 --> 02:32.247
I lived on a weed commune...

02:34.247 --> 02:37.247
...where we all shared in
the raising of the children.

02:38.757 --> 02:40.256
Oh, yeah, sure.
Well, it's easier that way

02:40.257 --> 02:42.247
when you're too stoned
to know whose kid is whose.

