03:27.248 --> 03:28.416
You okay?

03:28.417 --> 03:30.246
Ah, I'm short a guy at work.

03:30.247 --> 03:33.246
My back's acting up
from hangin' drywall.

03:33.247 --> 03:34.247
Turns out...

03:34.248 --> 03:36.246
I forgot to eat right
and exercise

03:36.247 --> 03:37.247
for the last 50 years.

03:39.247 --> 03:40.247
It's never too late.

03:40.248 --> 03:42.246
That's what they say, but...

03:42.247 --> 03:42.957
it is.

03:44.247 --> 03:46.246
Hey, Beck.

03:46.247 --> 03:47.247
What do you need?

03:47.248 --> 03:49.247
Willpower or a beer.

03:50.587 --> 03:52.247
Once again, we have a winner!

03:54.247 --> 03:56.246
Hey, you know what, Deej?

03:56.247 --> 03:57.756
If you want to pick up
a couple extra bucks,

03:57.757 --> 03:59.246
you could help out on my crew.

03:59.247 --> 04:00.256
I am slammed at work.

04:00.257 --> 04:02.246
You know the servicing
of vending machines,

04:02.247 --> 04:04.246
it's not just collecting coins.

04:04.247 --> 04:07.586
Vandals scratch curse words
into the glass.

04:07.587 --> 04:09.247
And they say
<i>firemen</i> are heroes.

04:12.247 --> 04:13.247
Hey, Dad?

04:13.248 --> 04:14.586
Mm-hmm?

04:14.587 --> 04:17.245
How come you didn't ask <i> me
</i> to do drywall?

04:17.247 --> 04:19.245
'Cause I'm a girl?
[ Sighs ]

04:19.247 --> 04:21.245
Wait, you're not
gonna get me with that one.

04:21.247 --> 04:23.247
No, I didn't ask you
because you're a <i> woman.</i>

04:25.757 --> 04:28.246
Come on. I could really
use the extra money.

04:28.247 --> 04:30.756
I'm saving to put a down payment
on a mobile home

04:30.757 --> 04:34.246
with a patio and a tree
that you can tie yourself to

04:34.247 --> 04:35.247
when the tornado comes.

04:37.247 --> 04:40.246
I'd love to, Beck,
but it's construction.

04:40.247 --> 04:41.756
I'm not comfortable
having you around

04:41.757 --> 04:44.246
all that rough language
and dirty jokes,

04:44.247 --> 04:45.247
and I don't think
I can cut back.

04:47.417 --> 04:49.957
Women built the pyramids, Dad.

04:51.757 --> 04:52.956
I don't know if that's true,

04:52.957 --> 04:55.246
but I like how quick
you came up with it.

04:55.247 --> 04:57.246
So, is that a yes?

04:57.247 --> 04:58.956
All right, Butch.
We'll give it a shot.

04:58.957 --> 04:59.757
Oh!

05:00.957 --> 05:02.246
And, Mom, we'll be fine.

05:02.247 --> 05:04.246
Don't text me every
five minutes when I'm
with Dad and Blue.

05:04.247 --> 05:06.246
I won't.

05:06.247 --> 05:08.246
Just remember, any
nice feelings you
have about her...

05:08.247 --> 05:09.247
hurt me.

05:11.247 --> 05:14.246
Are you jealous because
new mommy is so pretty?

05:14.247 --> 05:16.246
Ohh. That was rough.

05:16.247 --> 05:18.247
I'm a little wounded...
and kinda proud.

05:20.247 --> 05:23.246
Harris, you come
from a long line of
sharp-tongued women

05:23.247 --> 05:25.246
who have found that
this particular gift

05:25.247 --> 05:29.246
keeps them from having any
truly successful relationships

05:29.247 --> 05:30.247
outside the family.

05:33.247 --> 05:34.247
[ Knock on door, door opens ]

05:34.248 --> 05:36.246
Hey.
You got everything?

05:36.247 --> 05:37.247
Everything but happiness.

05:39.247 --> 05:41.246
I mean I'm working on it
with a new boyfriend.

05:41.247 --> 05:43.246
Sorry, I-I-I meant bags.

05:43.247 --> 05:44.756
Oh, yeah, we got baggage...

05:44.757 --> 05:46.246
but...
[Clears throat]

05:46.247 --> 05:48.246
we're aware of it,
and as a life coach,

05:48.247 --> 05:49.586
I know that once you're
aware of the problem,

05:49.587 --> 05:52.246
then you can begin
that long, long process.

05:52.247 --> 05:53.586
Uh, yeah...

05:53.587 --> 05:55.416
sensing that
you're still living alone?

05:55.417 --> 05:58.246
Uh, no, no,
I've got Bev with me now.

05:58.247 --> 06:00.246
Talking to her is a challenge.

06:00.247 --> 06:03.246
Did you know that
she was beautiful in her day

06:03.247 --> 06:05.247
but neither of her daughters
inherited that?

06:08.247 --> 06:09.247
[ Laughs nervously ]

06:16.247 --> 06:18.247
So strange being in
this house without your mom.

06:19.247 --> 06:20.416
When you and I
were having problems,

06:20.417 --> 06:23.126
she'd always take me aside
and say,

06:23.127 --> 06:25.247
"David, I can't understand you
when you're crying."

06:27.247 --> 06:30.247
- Well, you were the daughter she always wanted.
- [ Chuckles ]

06:32.247 --> 06:33.247
How you doing?

06:33.247 --> 06:34.247
Mm.

06:34.247 --> 06:35.247
Up and down.

06:36.257 --> 06:39.246
Well, things look like
they're going really
well with you and Blue.

06:39.247 --> 06:42.126
Yeah. Thank you for being
so accepting of it.

06:42.127 --> 06:43.246
Oh, yeah, no problem.

06:43.247 --> 06:45.246
Um... did you tell her

06:45.247 --> 06:47.246
that we slept together
like three months ago?

06:47.247 --> 06:49.247
I just need to know in case
I mention it in passing.

06:52.257 --> 06:54.247
Please do not do that.

06:55.757 --> 06:57.246
Okay, but let's
be brutally honest.

06:57.247 --> 07:00.416
After we had sex, you were
totally ready to ditch Blue.

07:00.417 --> 07:01.247
Well...

07:03.247 --> 07:04.247
It was great sex.

07:06.247 --> 07:08.247
Yeah. It was.

07:10.247 --> 07:13.246
[ Chuckling ] Don't --
Don't... confuse me.

07:13.247 --> 07:16.126
I-I really think I found
something that works.

07:16.127 --> 07:18.246
[ Scoffs ]
Really? With <i> her?</i>

07:18.247 --> 07:19.247
Yeah.

07:20.247 --> 07:22.247
Yes, I think
I found my soulmate.

07:26.247 --> 07:28.246
That's great.
[ Chuckles ]

07:28.247 --> 07:30.246
I mean, I just wanted clarity.

07:30.247 --> 07:31.756
As long as we're clear,
it's great.

07:31.757 --> 07:32.247
Hi, Dad.

07:34.247 --> 07:36.127
Oh, me. Yeah. Hi.
Hi, son.

07:38.247 --> 07:40.246
What happened
to your socks and shoes?

07:40.247 --> 07:41.247
We're grounding.

07:41.248 --> 07:44.126
Harris and I are
gonna do it this
weekend with Blue.

07:44.127 --> 07:46.586
She says it's a way
to be more connected
to Mother Earth.

07:46.587 --> 07:49.247
Uncle David's girlfriend, Blue,
says God is in the dirt.

07:51.247 --> 07:53.246
You replaced
this wonderful woman

07:53.247 --> 07:55.247
with "God is in the dirt"
woman?

08:01.247 --> 08:02.247
Great to see you, Geena.

08:02.248 --> 08:04.247
I see the war has softened you.

08:10.247 --> 08:13.246
Hello, everyone.
Name's Becky.

08:13.247 --> 08:16.246
Not gonna lie, I'm also
the boss's daughter.

08:16.247 --> 08:18.246
Just because I may own
this business one day

08:18.247 --> 08:19.957
should not affect
how you treat me.

08:25.247 --> 08:26.247
Good morning, Miss Healy.

08:26.248 --> 08:29.247
Nice to see you on time
for your first day.

08:31.247 --> 08:32.246
What's in here?

08:32.246 --> 08:33.246
Water. Duh!

08:34.246 --> 08:37.246
Water has bubbles
when you shake it.

08:37.246 --> 08:38.256
There's no bubbles
when I shake this.

08:38.256 --> 08:40.756
[ Sniffs ]
This vodka?

08:40.756 --> 08:42.246
Oh, my God.

08:42.246 --> 08:43.756
Okay...

08:43.756 --> 08:45.247
Who put vodka
in my water bottle?

08:46.757 --> 08:48.246
Dwight?

08:48.247 --> 08:49.957
So not cool, man.

08:51.247 --> 08:53.586
Guys, would you go out
and unload my truck?

08:53.587 --> 08:54.247
Thanks.

08:57.587 --> 08:59.246
What the hell's going on?

08:59.247 --> 09:00.756
It's 6:30
in the morning.

09:00.757 --> 09:02.246
Sorry, Dad.

09:02.247 --> 09:03.247
I usually take a shot

09:03.248 --> 09:05.416
before I start
at the restaurant.

09:05.417 --> 09:08.416
Sober Becky wasn't
getting really good tips.

09:08.417 --> 09:10.246
Here's a tip --

09:10.247 --> 09:11.247
if somebody gets hurt
on this job,

09:11.248 --> 09:12.756
I lose my license.

09:12.757 --> 09:14.956
That's why I have
a zero-tolerance policy

09:14.957 --> 09:16.956
for alcohol!

09:16.957 --> 09:18.247
And the union's okay with that?

09:20.247 --> 09:21.756
Is this going to be a problem?

09:21.757 --> 09:23.586
Okay, fine.

09:23.587 --> 09:26.246
Sober Becky it is.

09:26.247 --> 09:27.957
We'll all get to
know her together.

09:30.247 --> 09:31.586
How come those glasses
are still full?

09:31.587 --> 09:32.417
Ha ha!

09:32.418 --> 09:34.126
Señoritas' night.

09:34.127 --> 09:35.246
I-I <i> want</i> to have fun.

09:35.247 --> 09:37.956
I just keep thinking
about how David and
his crazy girlfriend

09:37.957 --> 09:39.246
are playing house with <i> my</i> kids.

09:39.247 --> 09:41.246
Well, you're here, you're out,

09:41.247 --> 09:42.756
you're two shots away
from losing Darlene

09:42.757 --> 09:43.417
and discovering...

09:43.418 --> 09:46.247
Dah-leenah!

09:50.247 --> 09:52.246
Look, I know it's hard to hear,

09:52.247 --> 09:55.246
but David found someone,
and so should you.

09:55.247 --> 09:57.246
There is a room
full of guys here.

09:57.247 --> 09:58.247
And you're a catch.

09:58.248 --> 09:59.956
You're an educated,

09:59.957 --> 10:02.127
diabetes-free woman in Lanford?

10:04.247 --> 10:05.247
There's only two of us.

10:06.257 --> 10:08.246
All right, let's make this
a drinking game.

10:08.247 --> 10:09.247
Every time we spot
a guy who looks like

10:09.248 --> 10:11.246
he doesn't have a job,
we take a drink,

10:11.247 --> 10:12.586
and then
you'll have the courage

10:12.587 --> 10:14.247
to approach the ones who <i> do.</i>

10:15.247 --> 10:16.247
I'm in.

10:17.257 --> 10:20.416
Plaid shirt at two o'clock.
Check it out.

10:20.417 --> 10:23.246
He's wearing a watch
with a <i> leather</i> band.

10:23.247 --> 10:25.246
Yeah, but nobody
wears a watch anymore.

10:25.247 --> 10:27.246
That means he can't
afford a phone.

10:27.247 --> 10:28.247
No job!

10:31.247 --> 10:32.247
Hey.

10:32.248 --> 10:34.246
That guy's stitches are even.

10:34.247 --> 10:36.246
Them there's doctor stitches.

10:36.247 --> 10:38.247
Healthcare -- job!

10:40.247 --> 10:42.416
If you're not gonna
hit that, I will.

10:42.417 --> 10:45.246
Okay, this is pathetic.

10:45.247 --> 10:47.246
Hunting for men or
our lives aren't complete?

10:47.247 --> 10:48.416
We're better than that.

10:48.417 --> 10:49.257
Excuse me.

10:49.258 --> 10:50.416
Sorry.

10:50.417 --> 10:51.586
Can I buy you a drink?

10:51.587 --> 10:53.246
Oh, hi.
Yeah, sure.

10:53.247 --> 10:54.247
Gin and tonic?

10:54.248 --> 10:56.246
Yes.

10:56.247 --> 10:57.247
While you're doing that,

10:57.248 --> 10:59.247
I'm gonna get the 411
on Stitches for ya.

11:01.247 --> 11:02.416
Uh, two gin and tonics, please.

11:02.417 --> 11:04.246
I'm sorry. W-What kind
of gin do you prefer?

11:04.247 --> 11:05.586
Oh, you choose.

11:05.587 --> 11:07.246
Sure, yeah, yeah.

11:07.247 --> 11:09.246
Sometimes the <i> man</i> chooses.
[ Chuckles ]

11:09.247 --> 11:11.246
Uh, well...

11:11.247 --> 11:14.246
Let's see, they got
the one with the fancy
English guard guy.

11:14.247 --> 11:16.246
But, you know,
once you put the tonic in,

11:16.247 --> 11:17.256
it most likely is gonna
taste the same anyway.

11:17.257 --> 11:18.956
You know what?

11:18.957 --> 11:20.246
We should probably
be looking at tonics.

11:20.247 --> 11:22.246
Uh, d-do you have
a list of tonics?

11:22.247 --> 11:24.246
Um...

11:24.247 --> 11:26.247
Two English guard guys
and your best tonic.

11:27.247 --> 11:29.246
Y-You're not
<i>with</i> somebody, right?

11:29.247 --> 11:32.246
Oh, no, I was,
but that was, like,

11:32.247 --> 11:33.247
20 years ago,
so I think I'm free.

11:33.248 --> 11:35.246
[ Chuckles ]

11:35.247 --> 11:36.956
Uh, I'm Darlene.

11:36.957 --> 11:37.957
I-I got to tell you, I --

11:37.958 --> 11:39.246
I love your curly hair.

11:39.247 --> 11:40.256
But you probably
hate it, right?

11:40.257 --> 11:42.246
Everybody always wants
what they don't have.

11:42.247 --> 11:43.586
I'm sorry.

11:43.587 --> 11:46.246
I'm sorry. I'm kind of
a direct person.

11:46.247 --> 11:47.756
I assume you're
talking to me because,

11:47.757 --> 11:51.246
at some point, you
want all this small
talk to lead to sex?

11:51.247 --> 11:52.247
It doesn't have to.

11:52.247 --> 11:53.247
No, no, no, it's okay.

11:53.247 --> 11:54.247
I'm seriously considering it.

11:58.247 --> 11:59.247
Stitches was a bust.

12:00.757 --> 12:02.246
[ Clears throat ]
Horse kicked him
in the head.

12:02.247 --> 12:03.247
He's not all there.

12:03.248 --> 12:08.956
♪♪

12:08.957 --> 12:09.957
Hey.

12:09.958 --> 12:11.246
Oh, hey. Hi, you.

12:11.247 --> 12:13.246
Uh, I was just on my way out.

12:13.247 --> 12:14.247
Let me get my shoes on.

12:16.247 --> 12:18.246
Do you mind if we go inside
and talk for a minute?

12:18.247 --> 12:19.756
Oh, yeah, just --
just a minute.

12:19.757 --> 12:22.247
I'm late to the place
I was clearly on my way to.

12:26.247 --> 12:28.246
I just thought I'd stop by
and give you an update

12:28.247 --> 12:30.256
on how things are going.

12:30.257 --> 12:32.126
Uh...

12:32.127 --> 12:33.256
Mark's fine and...

12:33.257 --> 12:35.247
Harris is fine, too.

12:36.247 --> 12:37.247
Why would you come over here

12:37.248 --> 12:39.126
to tell me everything's fine?

12:39.127 --> 12:40.756
All right, uh...

12:40.757 --> 12:43.247
Something happened
but nothing's <i> wrong.</i>

12:44.247 --> 12:46.247
Does it look like
I'm enjoying this game?

12:48.417 --> 12:51.246
Harris had a friend over, um...

12:51.247 --> 12:54.247
a boy...
and they had sex.

12:55.247 --> 12:57.246
What?!

12:57.247 --> 12:58.416
Wha-- How -- What do you --

12:58.417 --> 13:00.246
How could you let this happen?!

13:00.247 --> 13:02.246
I was at work and I-I know
that's no excuse

13:02.247 --> 13:04.246
and I-I feel horrible.

13:04.247 --> 13:05.247
Wait, w-why were you at work

13:05.248 --> 13:06.586
when you were supposed
to be watching our kids?!

13:06.587 --> 13:08.246
I couldn't help it.

13:08.247 --> 13:09.247
I started my job
at Trader Joe's,

13:09.247 --> 13:10.247
and they made me work overtime

13:10.248 --> 13:12.247
to do all the
stupid chalkboards.

13:15.247 --> 13:16.247
They really like my drawings,

13:16.248 --> 13:18.246
which makes me feel good,
but on the other hand --

13:18.247 --> 13:19.247
David!

13:19.248 --> 13:21.246
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

13:21.247 --> 13:23.586
Look, I-I-I was just as upset
as you are right now,

13:23.587 --> 13:25.246
but...

13:25.247 --> 13:27.246
here's the <i> good</i> news.

13:27.247 --> 13:29.246
Blue was there

13:29.247 --> 13:31.246
and Harris ended up
